# Project Architecture

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 14+ (App Router) with TypeScript (strict mode)
- Material UI (MUI) v6 + MUI X Charts

## Folder structure

- `config/` — app-wide configuration constants. Suffix: `.config.ts`
- `src/app/` — Next.js App Router pages and API routes
- `src/components/` — UI components following Atomic Design (atoms, molecules, organisms)
- `src/@types/` — shared TypeScript interfaces and type definitions
- `src/hooks/` — custom React hooks grouped by domain. Suffix: `.hooks.ts`
- `src/hooks/tables/` — table column/row definitions. Suffix: `.table.tsx`
- `src/contexts/` — React Context providers + consumer hooks. Suffix: `Context.tsx`
- `src/redux/` — Redux Toolkit store, slices, and provider
- `src/services/` — API calls and business logic. Suffix: `.service.ts`
- `src/server/` — server-only code (database clients, server utilities)
- `src/auth/` — authentication config, middleware, and constants
- `src/utils/` — pure, reusable functions (no React, no side effects). Suffix: `.util.ts`

## Co-located files

Components and pages may have co-located helper files in kebab-case:

- `.constants.ts` — local constants (single-use; shared constants go to `config/`)
- `.callbacks.ts` — extracted event handlers and async logic
- `.schema.ts` — Zod validation schemas
- `.types.ts` — local type definitions

## Components (Atomic Design)

- `atoms/` — smallest building blocks (badges, chips, icons, inputs)
- `molecules/` — compositions of atoms (cards, forms, dialogs)
- `organisms/` — full sections with business logic (wizards, dashboards, data tables)

## Key rules

- No `.find()` or `.filter()` calls in components — extract to utils or hooks
- No prop drilling — use Context or Redux for shared state
- No magic numbers — use named constants from `config/` or co-located `.constants.ts`
- Server Components by default; add `'use client'` only when state, effects, or event handlers are needed
- Database queries go through services (`src/services/`), which use clients from `src/server/`. Hooks in `src/hooks/` wrap services for component consumption.
- Complex multi-step state lives in Redux slices (`src/redux/slices/`). Auth and theme use React Context.
- API routes in `src/app/api/` handle server-side logic
